item.title: 贝恩资本结束与 KKR 的富士软体收购战
item.description: 美国私募股权公司贝恩资本（Bain Capital）周一表示，它将不会发起对富士软的要约收购，从而正式结束与竞争对手 KKR 对这家日本 IT 公司的收购战。【原文：U.S. private equity firm Bain Capital said on Monday it will not launch a tender offer for Fuji Soft , formally ending a takeover battle with rival KKR for the Japanese IT company.】

item.title: 澳大利亚博思格钢铁公司盈利超出预期，攀升至三年来的最高点
item.description: 澳大利亚博思格钢铁公司（BlueScope Steel）的股价周一创下逾三年新高，此前该公司半年基本利润超出市场预期，并对美国进口钢铁关税发表了乐观评论。【原文：Shares of Australia's BlueScope Steel hit a more than 3-year high on Monday after the steelmaker's half-year underlying profit surpassed market expectations and its upbeat commentary on U.S. tariffs on steel imports.】

item.title: 石油连续第四天下跌，因预期俄乌和平可能提升供应量
item.description: 周一，油价连续第四天下跌，原因是人们预期俄罗斯与乌克兰达成的和平协议可能会缓解扰乱供应流的制裁，以及人们担心全球关税战可能会减缓经济增长并削弱能源需求。【原文：Oil prices fell for a fourth day on Monday on expectations a Russia-Ukraine peace deal could ease sanctions disrupting supply flows and on concerns that global tariff wars could slow economic growth and weaken energy demand.】

item.title: 数据保护机构称韩国暂停下载 DeepSeek
item.description: 韩国数据保护机构周一表示，在DeepSeek承认没有考虑到该机构关于保护个人数据的一些规定后，中国人工智能应用程序DeepSeek在韩国的新下载已被暂停。【原文：South Korea's data protection authority on Monday said new downloads of the Chinese AI app DeepSeek had been suspended in the country after DeepSeek acknowledged failing to take into account some of the agency's rules on protecting personal data.】

item.title: 澳大利亚钢铁制造商博思格将特朗普的关税政策视为利好消息
item.description: 澳大利亚最大的钢铁制造商博思格钢铁公司（BlueScope Steel）首席执行官马克-瓦塞拉（Mark Vassella）周一表示，该公司将成为美国总统唐纳德-特朗普（Donald Trump）保护主义关税的受益者，他预计价格上涨将提高博思格在北美的利润。【原文：BlueScope Steel , Australia's largest steelmaker, will be a beneficiary of U.S. President Donald Trump's protectionist tariffs, CEO Mark Vassella said on Monday, saying that he expects higher prices to boost BlueScope's profits in North America.】

item.title: 受人工智能提振，高盛上调中国股市目标价
item.description: 高盛（Goldman Sachs）周一上调了中国股市的目标价，预计人工智能的应用将促进盈利增长，并可能带来 2000 亿美元的资金流入。【原文：Goldman Sachs raised its target price for Chinese stocks on Monday, estimating that AI adoption could boost earnings growth and potentially bring in $200 billion of inflows.】

item.title: 腾讯微信应用与 Deepseek 合作启动内测，腾讯一跃而起
item.description: 腾讯股价周一开盘将上涨 6.6%，此前该公司表示，其微信消息应用已与 Deepseek 展开内测，各公司竞相与中国正在崛起的人工智能初创公司建立联系。【原文：Shares of Tencent were set to open up 6.6% on Monday after the company said its Weixin messaging app has launched beta testing with Deepseek as firms race to link up with China's rising artificial intelligence start-up.】

item.title: 日元上涨；澳元和新西兰元在利率决议前持稳
item.description: 周一，日元因日本国内生产总值数据向好而上涨，而澳元和新西兰元在本周晚些时候的政策决定出台前基本持稳。【原文：The yen rose on Monday in a boost from upbeat Japanese GDP data, while the Australian and New Zealand dollars held broadly steady ahead of policy decisions later in the week.】

item.title: 亚洲股市多数上涨，GDP 向好提振日元
item.description: 周一，亚洲股市走高，原因是香港科技板块抢走了风头，而日本经济增长乐观，与美国零售销售报告疲软形成鲜明对比，从而抬高了日元对美元的汇率。【原文：Asia share markets crept higher on Monday as Hong Kong's tech sector stole the limelight, while upbeat Japanese economic growth contrasted with a weak U.S. retail sales report to lift the yen on the dollar.】

item.title: 资本支出强劲，日本第四季度经济增长快于预期
item.description: 日本政府周一公布的数据显示，日本经济在 10-12 月份按年率计算增长了 2.8%，这主要得益于企业支出的增长和好于预期的消费。【原文：Japan's economy expanded an annualised 2.8% in the October-December quarter, government data showed on Monday, backed by improved business spending and better-than-expected consumption.】

item.title: 调查显示，英国企业准备应对增税带来的冲击
item.description: 周一的调查显示，由于政府对企业增税，许多英国雇主打算提价和裁员，小企业的信心降至五年来的最低点。【原文：Many British employers intend to raise prices and cut headcount because of the government's tax increases on business, with confidence among small businesses falling to a five-year low, surveys showed on Monday.】

item.title: Rightmove 称，英国房地产市场开始感受到税制变化的拖累
item.description: 周一公布的一项调查显示，在房产购置税上调之前，英国新上市住宅要价上涨的势头已经减弱。【原文：A run-up in asking prices for newly listed homes in Britain has lost steam ahead of an increase in property purchase taxes, according to a survey published on Monday.】

item.title: 汇丰投资者支持首席执行官裁撤投资银行业务
item.description: 汇丰曾是一家业务遍及 100 多个国家的庞大银行，但在过去十年中，它的全球业务版图逐渐缩小，并退出了低回报业务。【原文：Once a sprawling bank spanning more than 100 countries, HSBC has spent the last decade slowly shrinking its global footprint and exiting low-return businesses.】

item.title: 澳大利亚 Perpetual 获得 KKR 对其财富和信托单位的新报价
item.description: 澳大利亚 Perpetual 公司周一证实，该公司收到了收购公司 KKR & Co 就其财富管理和企业信托业务提出的修订方案，但表示该方案包括的商业条款仍有待敲定。【原文：Australia's Perpetual confirmed on Monday it received a revised proposal for its wealth management and corporate trust businesses from buyout firm KKR & Co , but said the offer includes commercial terms that still need to be finalised.】

item.title: 早间竞价：美元、科技和关税延迟助推轮动交易
item.description: 亚洲市场前瞻【原文：A look at the day ahead in Asian markets.】

item.title: 独家报道五家伊拉克银行将被禁止美元交易
item.description: 两位直接了解此事的消息人士周日告诉路透社，伊拉克央行将禁止另外五家当地银行从事美元交易，此举是在与美国财政部官员会面后采取的，目的是打击洗钱、美元走私和其他违法行为。【原文：Iraq's central bank will ban five more local banks from engaging in U.S. dollar transactions, a move that comes after meetings with U.S. Treasury officials in efforts to combat money laundering, dollar smuggling and other violations, two sources with direct knowledge of the matter told Reuters on Sunday.】

item.title: 腾讯消息应用微信与 DeepSeek 合作启动内测
item.description: 腾讯表示，其微信应用程序的搜索功能正在测试访问 DeepSeek 的权限，这是中国占主导地位的消息应用程序采取的一项重大举措，因为各公司都在竞相与中国正在崛起的人工智能初创公司建立联系。【原文：Tencent said its Weixin app's search function is beta testing access to DeepSeek, a major move by the country's dominant messaging app as firms race to link up with China's rising artificial intelligence start-up.】

item.title: 中国央行行长称人民币稳定是全球金融稳定的关键
item.description: 中国央行行长周日表示，稳定的人民币汇率是全球金融和经济稳定的关键，中国政府将继续让市场在决定汇率方面发挥决定性作用。【原文：China's central bank governor said on Sunday a stable yuan currency has been key to global financial and economic stability and Beijing will continue to let the market play a decisive role in deciding the exchange rate.】

item.title: 英国《金融时报》报道：欧盟计划实施特朗普式的食品进口限制措施
item.description: 据英国《金融时报》周日报道，为保护本国农民，欧盟计划阻止进口某些按照不同标准生产的食品，以呼应美国总统唐纳德-特朗普的对等贸易政策。【原文：The European Union plans to block imports of certain foodstuffs made to different standards in an effort to protect its farmers, echoing U.S. President Donald Trump's reciprocal trade policy, the Financial Times reported on Sunday.】

item.title: 埃隆-马斯克称 xAI 的 Grok 3 聊天机器人将于下周一亮相
item.description: 亿万富翁埃隆-马斯克（Elon Musk）周六表示，他的 xAI 人工智能聊天机器人和 ChatGPT 挑战者 Grok 3 将于太平洋时间周一晚上 8 点（格林尼治标准时间周二 4 点）发布，并进行现场演示。【原文：Billionaire Elon Musk said on Saturday that his xAI's artificial intelligence chatbot and ChatGPT challenger Grok 3 would be released with a live demo at 8 p.m. Pacific time on Monday (0400 GMT on Tuesday).】

item.title: 犹他州公共工会被禁止与州政府进行集体谈判
item.description: 在犹他州议会大厦举行了两周的抗议活动后，该州禁止了教师、警察、消防员和其他公职人员的集体谈判，工会誓言要与此举抗争。【原文：After two weeks of protests at the Utah state capitol, the state has banned collective bargaining for teachers, police officers, firefighters and other public employees, a move unions have vowed to fight.】

item.title: 据《华尔街日报》报道，博通、台积电盯上了英特尔可能进行的交易，这将拆分历史悠久的芯片制造商
item.description: 据《华尔街日报》周六援引知情人士的话报道，英特尔的竞争对手台湾半导体制造公司（Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co.【原文：Intel's rivals Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co and Broadcom are each eyeing potential deals that would break the U.S. chipmaking icon in two, the Wall Street Journal reported on Saturday, citing people familiar with the matter.】

item.title: 住房紧缩之际，澳大利亚将禁止外国人购买现房两年
item.description: 澳大利亚政府周日表示，将在两年内禁止外国投资者在该国购买现房，以增加压力过大的住房供应。【原文：Australia will ban foreign investors from buying existing homes in the country for two years, its government said on Sunday, in an effort to boost under-pressure housing supply.】

item.title: 米莱兜售加密货币后，阿根廷反对党威胁进行弹劾审判
item.description: 总裁哈维尔-米莱（Javier Milei）在 X 上发布了推荐鲜为人知的加密钱币 $LIBRE的帖子，不久之后，该钱币就飙升至每枚近 5 美元。几小时后，它又跌至 1 美元以下。【原文：President Javier Milei posted on X recommending the little-known crypto coin $LIBRE, which soon after shot up to nearly $5 apiece. Hours later, it plummeted to under $1.】

item.title: 亚马逊北卡罗来纳州员工拒绝加入工会，零售商在劳工斗争中获胜
item.description: 北卡罗来纳州的亚马逊工人周六投票反对加入工会，这对这家零售巨头来说是一个重大胜利，因为它一直极力反对在全美各地的工厂组织工会。【原文：Amazon workers in North Carolina voted on Saturday against joining a union, a big win for the retail giant which has vigorously opposed organized labor at its facilities across the United States.】

item.title: 根据新规定，加拿大银行必须披露董事会和高层管理人员的多样性
item.description: 根据周六公布的新规定，加拿大银行和其他国家机构必须披露其董事会和高层管理人员的多样性信息，这与美国特朗普政府终止此类做法形成了鲜明对比。【原文：Canadian banks and other national institutions have to disclose information about the diversity of their boards of directors and top management under new rules published on Saturday, in sharp contrast with the U.S. Trump administration which is ending such practices.】

item.title: 北卡罗来纳州亚马逊工会候选人指控选举计票受到干扰
item.description: 北卡罗来纳州一个新成立的工会声称，亚马逊周六在罗利附近的一个仓库干扰了计票过程。【原文：An upstart union in North Carolina alleged Amazon interfered with the vote counting process on Saturday at a warehouse near Raleigh.】

item.title: 据彭博社报道，苹果旨在为 Vision Pro 带来人工智能功能和空间内容应用程序
item.description: 据彭博新闻社周六报道，苹果公司正计划为其 Vision Pro 头戴式耳机添加苹果智能，并最早于 4 月份更新访客用户模式和空间内容应用程序。【原文：Apple is planning to add Apple Intelligence to its Vision Pro headset, along with an updated mode for guest users and a spatial content app as early as April, Bloomberg News reported on Saturday.】

item.title: 特朗普参观波音飞机，强调新空军一号迟迟未到位
item.description: 白宫表示，唐纳德-特朗普总统周六参观了一架波音飞机，以强调空军一号新飞机交付的延误。【原文：President Donald Trump toured a Boeing plane on Saturday to highlight delays in delivering new Air Force One aircraft, said the White House.】

item.title: 巴库钢铁公司、金达尔公司成为收购意大利伊尔瓦公司的领跑者
item.description: 意大利政府周六表示，巴库钢铁公司和金达尔国际钢铁公司已经提高了对Acciaierie d'Italia（ADI）（前称Ilva）的出价，使它们成为该工厂竞标的领跑者。【原文：Baku Steel Company and Jindal Steel International have raised their bids for Acciaierie d'Italia (ADI), formerly known as Ilva, the Italian government said on Saturday, making them the frontrunners in the bidding for the plant.】
